South Africa Union Declares Wage Dispute With Petroleum Industry Employers

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-06-01T12:52:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/south-africa-union-declares-wage-dispute-with-petroleum-industry-employers.html
South Africa ’s Solidarity labor union
said it declared a wage dispute with employers in the country’s
petroleum industry following two rounds of talks.  Petroleum companies in South Africa include  Sasol Ltd (SOL) ,
PetroSA Ltd. and Engen Ltd.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
